● The MTL4 → MTL5 migration is complete. Here's a summary of all changes:

  Submodule swap:
  - Removed ext/stillwater-sc/mtl4, added ext/stillwater-sc/mtl5
  - Updated .gitmodules

  Directory rename:
  - src/mtl4ext/ → src/mtlext/

  CMakeLists.txt updates (4 files):
  - Root: MTL5 submodule (unconditional, no Boost needed), disabled MTL5 tests/examples, added MTL5 include paths (source + generated)
  - src/solvers/: include path → mtl5/include
  - benchmark/performance/: include path → mtl5/include
  - benchmark/: removed if(Boost_FOUND) guard around performance benchmark

  Source file API migration (5 files):
  - #include <boost/numeric/mtl/mtl.hpp> → #include <mtl/mtl.hpp>
  - mtl::Collection<M>::value_type → typename M::value_type (Collection is now a concept)
  - mtl::traits::enable_if_vector/matrix → requires mtl::Vector<V> / requires mtl::Matrix<M>
  - M[i][j] → M(i,j) (dense2D uses operator() in MTL5)
  - Inserter pattern → direct A(r,c) = value assignment (inserter is sparse-only in MTL5)
  - A = 0.0 → mtl::set_to_zero(A) or explicit loops
  - inv = Scalar(1) → explicit identity loop
  - mtl::mat::qr(A, Q, R) → mtl::qr_factor(A, tau) + mtl::qr_extract_Q(A, tau)

  MTL5 fix (identity.hpp, mtl_fwd.hpp):
  - Removed static constexpr from identity values to support non-literal types like boost::multiprecision::cpp_bin_float_quad

  Documentation: Updated CLAUDE.md and README.md references from mtl4 to mtl5.

